German Carmakers Oppose S. Korea Trade Pact, Handelsblatt Says

-- B y   H o l g e r   E l f e s
-- 
2011-07-04T06:17:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-04/german-carmakers-oppose-s-korea-trade-pact-handelsblatt-says.html
Germany ’s auto industry is opposed to
a free trade agreement between the European Union and  South
Korea  as it carries disadvantages for European car makers
compared to Korean competitors,  Handelsblatt  reported, citing
Matthias Wissmann, who heads the VDA, the German carmakers’
association.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Holger Elfes in Dusseldorf at 
 helfes@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editors responsible for this story:
Celeste Perri at   cperri@bloomberg.net . 